  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Validation results are reported against published experimental datasets; one result references the Bludszuweit (1995) power-law hemolysis correlation as the comparator basis without providing a machine-readable comparedAgainst link. The remaining validation result carries a comparedAgainst reference to a steady-flow benchtop dataset, which was acquired at a fixed impeller speed of 2500 RPM and a single flow rate of 5 L/min — conditions that do not span the five flow-speed combinations required by the COU. The mismatch is not flagged in the validation narrative. Decision recorded as Accepted.",
